01:41.739 --> 01:44.374
(inhales, exhales)

01:44.442 --> 01:46.609
You're right--
it's not zucchini,

01:46.677 --> 01:48.144
it's okra.

01:48.212 --> 01:50.180
I guess when I
was at the store,

01:50.247 --> 01:51.581
my mind was
somewhere else.

01:51.649 --> 01:53.149
See, sometimes I escape

01:53.217 --> 01:55.068
to a little place
in my head

01:55.136 --> 01:57.954
where no one complains
about the meals I cook.

01:58.022 --> 02:00.457
(gasping)

02:00.524 --> 02:04.027
And there's no more scraping snot
rockets off the shower tiles.

02:05.329 --> 02:08.298
And no more PB&J
with the crusts cut off.

02:08.365 --> 02:11.000
(bones crack)

02:11.068 --> 02:13.403
Anyway, if you
don't want to eat it,

02:13.471 --> 02:15.905
I can fix something else.

02:15.973 --> 02:18.508
Okra's great!
Yum!

02:18.576 --> 02:19.776
Well, I'm not eating it.

02:19.844 --> 02:21.344
Okra gives me pretty bad gas.

02:21.412 --> 02:22.212
Just eat it.

02:22.279 --> 02:23.513
Okay.

02:23.581 --> 02:25.849
But don't complain
if I get pretty bad gas.

02:25.916 --> 02:28.151
(smoke alarm beeping)

02:28.219 --> 02:30.987
(coughing)

02:31.055 --> 02:32.455
Stan!
(coughing)

02:32.523 --> 02:34.157
The house must
be on fire!

02:34.225 --> 02:36.409
(all coughing)

02:36.477 --> 02:37.911
I don't see any flames.

02:37.978 --> 02:39.362
Then what is it?!

02:39.430 --> 02:40.463
(beeping continues)

02:40.531 --> 02:41.798
(groans)
Who farted?

02:41.866 --> 02:43.199
This guy!

02:43.267 --> 02:46.703
(farting)

02:50.253 --> 02:52.779
Well, whatever's in there
is off-the-charts toxic.

02:53.081 --> 02:55.850
It's gonna take at least a
week to sanitize your house.

02:55.854 --> 02:56.954
A week?!

02:57.122 --> 02:59.123
Where are we supposed
to go for a week?

02:59.190 --> 03:00.791
Relax. Just leave it to me.

03:05.207 --> 03:07.676
Okay, I got us free rooms
for the whole week.

03:07.718 --> 03:10.352
How'd you do that?
I stayed here back in the '80s

03:10.420 --> 03:11.954
and suffered
a terrible accident.

03:12.022 --> 03:15.391
To avoid a lawsuit, the hotel gave me
a free week of rooms.

03:15.459 --> 03:17.693
Honestly, I forgot about
the whole thing until today.

03:17.761 --> 03:19.729
That fart really shook
some memories loose.

03:19.796 --> 03:22.598
Wow, I just remembered,
I was also in a legal battle

03:22.666 --> 03:23.999
with Nabisco.

03:24.067 --> 03:27.002
I claimed I was Asian
and sued over Cheese Nips.

03:27.070 --> 03:28.637
Anyway, everything's
complimentary--

03:28.705 --> 03:30.940
room service, laundry, you name it.
You hear that, honey?

03:31.007 --> 03:33.609
A whole week without you
having to take care of us.

03:33.677 --> 03:35.745
Wow! Finally
some me time.

03:35.812 --> 03:38.314
Stan and Francine,
here are keys to <i>your</i> room.

03:38.381 --> 03:39.648
And, Steve,
here's yours.

03:39.716 --> 03:40.783
What about
my room?

03:40.851 --> 03:41.884
Got you covered.

03:44.521 --> 03:46.622
Oh, boy, what's in here?

03:48.792 --> 03:51.727
MALE NARRATOR:
<i>Some say that was the end</i>
<i>of Klaus's story.</i>

03:51.795 --> 03:54.029
<i>Some say it was</i>
<i>just the beginning.</i>

03:54.097 --> 03:57.566
<i>No one ever says</i>
<i>it was the middle.</i>

04:00.737 --> 04:02.505
♪ ♪

04:16.086 --> 04:18.220
Bewitching,
isn't she?

04:18.288 --> 04:19.721
I know you.

04:19.790 --> 04:22.291
Weren't you the concierge
in <i>Pretty Woman?</i>

04:22.359 --> 04:24.527
(chuckles)
Yes. I'm Hector Elizondo.

04:24.594 --> 04:28.464
I've played a concierge in
over 400 movies and TV pilots.

04:28.532 --> 04:32.067
Acting pays the bills
so I can pursue my true passion:

04:32.135 --> 04:34.570
concierging.

04:34.638 --> 04:37.273
I don't mean to ignore
your strange monologue, but...

04:37.340 --> 04:39.809
I can't take my eyes
off this enchanting vision.

04:39.876 --> 04:43.646
The moment I saw her,
I felt as I'd... met her before.

04:43.713 --> 04:46.816
Impossible. The great artist
Patrick Nagel painted her

04:46.883 --> 04:48.684
while staying
in this hotel...

04:48.752 --> 04:50.419
in 1981.

04:50.487 --> 04:52.521
Then I'm too late
to meet her.

04:52.589 --> 04:55.024
God! If it were
only 1981 again!

04:55.091 --> 04:58.828
Well, young man...
perhaps it can be.

05:00.163 --> 05:02.698
Excuse me, where can
I get some tampons?

05:02.766 --> 05:04.066
Right over here, miss.

05:04.134 --> 05:06.268
I keep them next to my Tony.

05:13.143 --> 05:16.645
Huh. No breakfast to make,
no clothes to wash.

05:16.713 --> 05:19.448
I guess I can do
whatever I want.

05:27.624 --> 05:28.991
What are you doing?

05:29.059 --> 05:31.193
Laying out your
clothes for the day.

05:31.261 --> 05:32.995
Honey, stop worrying about us.

05:33.063 --> 05:35.798
Go spend time with Francine,
get to know her.

05:35.866 --> 05:38.200
That's something
I always wish <i>I'd</i> done.

05:38.268 --> 05:40.336
A-Are you sure?

05:40.403 --> 05:43.105
(laughs)
I'm pretty sure
I can dress myself.

05:43.173 --> 05:44.607
Uh, o-okay.

05:44.674 --> 05:46.575
I'll just...

05:46.643 --> 05:49.111
get to know me.

05:49.179 --> 05:50.813
(door closes)

05:50.881 --> 05:52.414
Oop, she forgot the socks.

05:54.351 --> 05:56.552
Now, which ones
go with the suit,

05:56.620 --> 05:58.754
navy or black?

05:58.822 --> 06:00.289
Francine!

06:00.357 --> 06:01.857
Do you like horseback riding?

06:01.925 --> 06:04.093
Hang gliding?
I-I don't know.

06:04.160 --> 06:06.495
Okay. How <i>do</i> you
spend your time?

06:06.563 --> 06:08.564
Well, for the last 20 years,

06:08.632 --> 06:10.799
I've just taken care
of my family.

06:10.867 --> 06:13.602
Sounds like someone
needs to get a life.

06:13.670 --> 06:16.972
(soft stammering)

06:17.040 --> 06:19.341
ELIZONDO:
<i>Sounds like someone</i>
<i>needs to get a life...</i>

06:19.409 --> 06:21.510
<i>get a life... get a life...</i>

06:23.179 --> 06:24.380
Do you know Sarah Blanch,

06:24.447 --> 06:26.048
the OmniSlab concrete
rep from Chicago?

06:26.116 --> 06:28.717
No, but I hear she's finally coming
to one of these conventions.

06:28.785 --> 06:31.553
I just heard she was in an
accident on her way here.

06:31.621 --> 06:33.622
Car went over a cliff
and into a river.

06:33.690 --> 06:35.891
That's horrible!
She's presumed dead.

06:35.959 --> 06:37.927
But nothing's <i>concrete.</i>

06:37.994 --> 06:39.728
(both laugh hysterically)

06:39.796 --> 06:42.064
But seriously,
she's probably dead.

06:44.868 --> 06:47.202
I know who you are!
You do?

06:47.270 --> 06:49.071
There's only one name tag left.

06:49.139 --> 06:50.773
You must be Sarah Blanch.

06:50.840 --> 06:53.108
ELIZONDO:
Someone needs to get a life...

06:53.176 --> 06:54.443
get a life...

06:54.511 --> 06:56.145
get a life...

06:56.212 --> 06:57.813
Y... es!

06:57.881 --> 07:00.382
That's me!
I am Sarah Blanch.

07:02.385 --> 07:04.853
Someone needs
to get naked...

07:04.921 --> 07:07.589
get naked...
get naked...

07:07.657 --> 07:10.192
Please, God,
not you...

07:10.260 --> 07:11.894
not you...
not you...

07:15.973 --> 07:18.275
So, welcome everyone, and, uh,

07:18.342 --> 07:20.577
let's make this
concrete sellers convention

07:20.645 --> 07:23.046
the most solid one ever.

07:23.114 --> 07:24.747
(chuckling)

07:25.917 --> 07:27.250
Sarah Blanch!

07:27.318 --> 07:30.287
Pam Deakins!
The Bakersfield rep!

07:30.354 --> 07:32.389
We've done business
on the phone!

07:32.456 --> 07:33.857
Oh...!

07:33.925 --> 07:36.393
<i>Bakersfield</i> Pam!

07:36.460 --> 07:39.563
You know, Sarah, there's
a rumor that you died in a

07:39.630 --> 07:41.031
(whispers): car crash.

07:41.098 --> 07:43.099
(laughing): A what?

07:43.167 --> 07:44.801
Oh, my, no!

07:44.869 --> 07:47.370
I was just <i>dying</i>
to be here!

07:47.438 --> 07:49.773
(laughter)
If you're like me,

07:49.840 --> 07:52.642
you were dying to get away
from your family for a week.

07:52.710 --> 07:54.511
Actually, I...

07:54.579 --> 07:56.546
don't have a family.

07:56.614 --> 08:00.050
Nope. My life is all about me.

08:00.117 --> 08:03.219
Horseback riding
and hang gliding

08:03.287 --> 08:04.788
and, um...

08:04.855 --> 08:07.591
having sex with some of
Chicago's many Polacks.

08:07.658 --> 08:09.859
ROGER:
Sounds like
the life to me!

08:09.927 --> 08:11.161
Hi, Sarah.
Pete Pendelman,

08:11.228 --> 08:12.896
concrete man
out of Pheboygan.

08:12.963 --> 08:14.247
Let's walk and talk.

08:14.315 --> 08:15.882
What are you doing?

08:15.950 --> 08:18.852
What? On a whim, I decided
to be a saleswoman

08:18.920 --> 08:20.887
who didn't show
up-- big deal.

08:20.955 --> 08:23.657
No, I-I get it-- you need
a little escape from Francine.

08:23.724 --> 08:25.942
We are gonna have
so much fun this week!

08:26.010 --> 08:29.312
Yeah. We'll mingle,
go to cocktail mixers...

08:29.380 --> 08:32.015
Oh, no-- Pete Pendelman
is a recovering alcoholic.

08:32.082 --> 08:34.851
I started hitting the bottle
after my wife died...

08:34.919 --> 08:38.054
during breast reduction surgery
that I made her get.

08:38.121 --> 08:40.490
(choked up):
She was pregnant at the time!

08:40.558 --> 08:42.359
Anyway, we're
gonna have a blast--

08:42.426 --> 08:45.161
as long as the real
Sarah Blanch doesn't show up.

08:45.229 --> 08:47.597
Oh, don't worry--
Sarah Blanch is dead.

08:53.521 --> 08:54.721
(gasps)

08:54.805 --> 08:57.107
(laughing)

08:57.174 --> 08:58.508
(thud)

09:00.911 --> 09:02.846
Stop torturing
yourself, Steve.

09:02.913 --> 09:04.414
You'll never
have her...

09:04.482 --> 09:06.249
unless you believe in...

09:06.317 --> 09:07.851
time travel!

09:09.987 --> 09:11.321
What?

09:11.389 --> 09:13.623
Oh, sorry,
wrong brochure.

09:13.691 --> 09:16.192
Whoa! This claims you
could travel back in time

09:16.260 --> 09:17.894
using only your mind!

09:17.962 --> 09:19.629
Do you know
what this means?

09:19.697 --> 09:22.666
Yes. You can go back in
time, watch me be born,

09:22.733 --> 09:25.335
and be the first
person to hold me.

09:25.403 --> 09:26.870
Just kidding!

09:26.937 --> 09:29.773
Go back to 1981 and
get your dream girl!

09:29.840 --> 09:32.375
Thanks, Hector!

09:32.443 --> 09:36.146
Who will hug baby Hector?

09:39.917 --> 09:41.251
You tap-dance, too?

09:41.318 --> 09:42.485
Wow, Sarah!

09:42.553 --> 09:44.254
How many hobbies
do you have?

09:44.321 --> 09:45.288
Five.

09:45.356 --> 09:46.589
Wow!
Five?

09:46.657 --> 09:47.957
Pete, you've been quiet.

09:48.025 --> 09:49.459
What about your family?
You married?

09:51.062 --> 09:55.532
Two years ago my wife was killed
by a plastic surgeon in Ecuador.

09:55.599 --> 09:57.233
I found him on Yelp.

09:57.301 --> 09:59.035
I gave him two stars.

09:59.103 --> 10:02.939
Her breasts looked amazing
during the open-casket.

10:03.007 --> 10:05.809
So I... <i>was</i> married.

10:07.478 --> 10:10.113
(clears throat)

10:10.181 --> 10:11.681
(beep)

10:14.051 --> 10:15.051
(sighs)

10:15.119 --> 10:17.120
Looks like Sarah's
day is over.

10:17.188 --> 10:18.204
Aw...
Aw...

10:18.272 --> 10:19.823
Excuse me, Miss Blanch.

10:19.890 --> 10:24.027
We show you still haven't checked
into your executive suite.

10:26.697 --> 10:28.298
Whoa!

10:28.365 --> 10:31.267
A complimentary
bucket of Coronas?!

10:31.335 --> 10:33.603
Sarah must be
super important!

10:35.956 --> 10:38.508
Hey, let's order huge
sundaes from room service

10:38.576 --> 10:40.410
and just pig out!

10:40.478 --> 10:43.246
Oh, no sweets for Pete--
I have stage two diabetes.

10:43.314 --> 10:44.414
In fact...

10:44.482 --> 10:45.648
(inhales)

10:47.218 --> 10:48.485
(sucking)

10:48.552 --> 10:49.719
(quiet grunt)

10:49.787 --> 10:52.388
Really?

10:54.658 --> 10:57.660
I could get used
to being Sarah Blanch.

10:59.063 --> 11:01.564
♪ ♪

11:20.668 --> 11:23.286
How the hell does she
know how to tap-dance?

11:23.337 --> 11:26.673
Because she's Sarah
(bleep) Blanch!

11:26.757 --> 11:28.191
Hey!

11:28.259 --> 11:29.709
You're a
loudmouth, Doug.

11:29.794 --> 11:31.678
You're loud.

11:31.762 --> 11:33.263
All right, Steve,

11:33.330 --> 11:37.367
this is exactly how your
hotel room looked in 1981.

11:37.434 --> 11:39.302
Whoa. A waterbed!

11:41.205 --> 11:42.772
So, basically,

11:42.840 --> 11:45.975
I just concentrate as hard
as I can that I'm in 1981,

11:46.043 --> 11:48.244
and I'll be transported
back in time

11:48.312 --> 11:50.213
to meet my dream girl
from the painting?

11:50.281 --> 11:51.514
Yes, Steve.

11:51.582 --> 11:54.250
What is so hard
to understand about that?

11:54.318 --> 11:57.787
Okay, it's May 14, 1981.

11:57.855 --> 12:00.957
President Jimmy Carter leaves
the White House in disgrace.

12:01.025 --> 12:03.159
Pope John Paul II
is shot in Rome

12:03.227 --> 12:05.195
by a deranged Jimmy Carter.

12:05.262 --> 12:08.832
Jimmy Carter kidnaps and devours
13 Christian babies.

12:08.899 --> 12:11.334
Hmm. Maybe I should have read
a real history book

12:11.402 --> 12:13.269
instead of the one Dad wrote.

12:16.974 --> 12:18.975
Did it work? Is it 1981?

12:24.081 --> 12:25.215
Roger?!

12:25.282 --> 12:26.749
Damn it, it didn't work.

12:26.817 --> 12:28.084
Who's Roger?

12:28.152 --> 12:30.920
The name's Reaganomics
Lamborghini, Jacuzzi dealer.

12:30.988 --> 12:34.123
Want to smoke cocaine out of my
pipe made from a Rubik's Cube?

12:34.191 --> 12:36.459
(yelling)

12:38.696 --> 12:40.496
Sir, are you
all right?!

12:40.564 --> 12:42.031
I was sitting on
this waterbed

12:42.099 --> 12:43.416
minding my own
my business

12:43.484 --> 12:44.517
when it spontaneously exploded!

12:44.585 --> 12:46.252
I demand a week
of free rooms,

12:46.320 --> 12:47.921
or I'll sue the
crap of you!

12:47.988 --> 12:49.355
Wait a second.

12:53.844 --> 12:55.078
I made it!

12:55.145 --> 12:57.013
It's 1981.

12:57.081 --> 12:58.982
♪ ♪

13:06.457 --> 13:08.157
Hey, I just got
another crazy text

13:08.225 --> 13:09.759
from Stan about socks.

13:09.827 --> 13:11.060
Is he okay?

13:11.111 --> 13:12.195
Oh, I'm sure
he's fine.

13:12.263 --> 13:14.397
(crying)

13:20.738 --> 13:23.573
Look, I don't have time
for anyone else right now.

13:23.641 --> 13:25.475
I'm too busy
living my own life.

13:25.542 --> 13:26.776
But it's not your life.

13:26.844 --> 13:28.077
It belongs to...

13:28.145 --> 13:29.612
Sarah, where
have you been?

13:29.680 --> 13:31.147
You have to
give your speech.

13:31.215 --> 13:32.882
What?

13:32.950 --> 13:35.318
There she is, our
closing speaker,

13:35.386 --> 13:38.588
OmniSlab rep,
Sarah Blanch.

13:38.656 --> 13:40.690
All right, you've taken Sarah
as far as she can go.

13:40.758 --> 13:41.891
Let's make a run for it.

13:41.959 --> 13:43.393
Come on up, Sarah.

13:46.430 --> 13:48.264
(inhales deeply)

13:50.768 --> 13:53.336
You... dumb bitch.

14:01.679 --> 14:03.279
Hello.

14:03.347 --> 14:06.599
Um, I'm here to talk about...

14:06.667 --> 14:11.170
rebar placement and planned
gap structure coordination.

14:11.238 --> 14:12.538
Huh?!

14:14.325 --> 14:16.192
(inhales deeply)

14:16.260 --> 14:17.660
You know what?

14:17.728 --> 14:19.295
No.

14:19.363 --> 14:22.765
What I'd really like
to talk about is the, um...

14:22.833 --> 14:24.734
uh... uh...

14:26.003 --> 14:28.237
The Chinese.

14:29.273 --> 14:30.773
The Chinese threat

14:30.841 --> 14:32.976
to our domestic
concrete industry.

14:34.111 --> 14:35.745
There are over a million

14:35.813 --> 14:38.481
Chinese people in China alone.

14:38.549 --> 14:42.085
And I'm here to tell you,
they are a-coming, folks.

14:42.152 --> 14:44.721
They know math,
they know kung-fu,

14:44.788 --> 14:48.157
and they've been going pee-pee
in our Coke for years!

14:48.225 --> 14:52.161
So let's keep the yella out
of our red, white and blue.

14:52.229 --> 14:53.496
(whooping, cheering
and applause)

14:53.564 --> 14:55.364
WOMAN:
Way to go, Sarah!

14:57.167 --> 14:58.434
MAN:
Yeah!

15:04.708 --> 15:06.542
Nagel,
you're a genius!

15:06.610 --> 15:08.444
Sun-faded prints
of your paintings

15:08.512 --> 15:11.247
will never be found
in Korean hair salons.

15:13.984 --> 15:16.319
Mr. Nagel, sir,

15:16.387 --> 15:18.788
I have traveled a great
distance to see you.

15:18.856 --> 15:20.923
You paint
my dream girl today,

15:20.991 --> 15:22.625
and I need to know
who she is.

15:22.693 --> 15:25.828
Oh, I'm touched
by your passion, young man.

15:25.896 --> 15:28.865
I'll help you
on your lover's quest,

15:28.932 --> 15:32.468
but first,
share in some cherry wine.

15:34.571 --> 15:38.207
Um, cherry wine
tastes pretty weird.

15:38.275 --> 15:41.844
That's because I put a bunch
of weird illegal things in it!

15:41.912 --> 15:44.714
(laughter)

15:44.782 --> 15:46.616
Nagel, you
son of a bitch,

15:46.683 --> 15:48.785
let's drug
some kids.

15:48.852 --> 15:50.653
Oh, you kidding me?

15:50.721 --> 15:52.321
You already cut
the turkey?

15:55.125 --> 15:56.492
Well, Sarah,
it's been fun,

15:56.560 --> 15:58.628
but all good characters
must to come end.

15:58.695 --> 16:00.163
Sarah, Jed Farnsworth

16:00.230 --> 16:02.131
of The Cherino
Concrete Corporation.

16:02.199 --> 16:04.500
I haven't heard someone speak
with that much passion

16:04.568 --> 16:06.769
since my fat friend
discovered Buca di Beppo.

16:06.837 --> 16:09.138
Wow. Thank you.

16:09.206 --> 16:11.908
Look, I want you to come manage
my Portland facility.

16:11.975 --> 16:15.578
It's the most prestigious job
in the concrete industry.

16:15.646 --> 16:17.547
I... I don't
know what to say.

16:17.614 --> 16:20.483
Say yes, and tomorrow,
you can fly to your new life

16:20.551 --> 16:23.853
in Economy Plus
with only one stop in Denver.

16:24.988 --> 16:26.289
What are you doing?

16:26.356 --> 16:27.757
What's there to
even think about?

16:27.825 --> 16:29.125
You're right.

16:29.193 --> 16:30.560
Mr. Farnsworth?

16:30.627 --> 16:32.361
I'll take that
job in Portland.

16:32.429 --> 16:33.963
Wait. What?!

16:34.031 --> 16:36.265
(sighs)

16:36.333 --> 16:38.067
Well, there goes
my two-year chip.

16:39.837 --> 16:42.038
Stale as the dickens.

16:42.106 --> 16:44.474
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Thank you to Timothy Crehan</i>
<i>of Salina, Kansas</i>

16:44.541 --> 16:46.742
<i>for sending us this week's</i>
<i>winning joke.</i>

16:52.180 --> 16:54.665
Francine, you're not actually
taking the job in Portland?

16:54.732 --> 16:56.333
Think about your family.

16:56.401 --> 16:58.101
Francine Smith
spent her whole life

16:58.169 --> 17:00.871
thinking about her family,
and what did it do for her?

17:00.939 --> 17:02.072
Nada.

17:03.441 --> 17:04.741
Francine, listen to me...

17:04.809 --> 17:06.108
Wait. You throwing that away?

17:06.176 --> 17:08.045
This would make a perfect cape.

17:09.213 --> 17:12.049
I am The Tender Vigilante.

17:13.984 --> 17:17.621
This city's in pain,
and it needs my tender justice.

17:19.223 --> 17:21.892
Oh, my God, it's working!

17:21.960 --> 17:23.226
(horns honking, thudding)

17:23.294 --> 17:24.795
(car alarm blaring)

17:27.031 --> 17:28.699
NAGEL:
Hey, Sleepyhead.

17:28.766 --> 17:30.434
Wha... What happened?

17:30.501 --> 17:32.135
You passed out.

17:32.203 --> 17:33.704
It's a shame.

17:33.771 --> 17:37.374
You missed the creation
of my latest masterpiece.

17:38.276 --> 17:39.643
She was here?!

17:39.711 --> 17:41.178
And I missed her?!

17:41.245 --> 17:43.246
No, my dear Smurf,

17:43.314 --> 17:45.215
you <i>are</i> her!

17:45.283 --> 17:47.150
While you slumbered,
I stripped you naked,

17:47.218 --> 17:50.487
placed a black wig on you,
put a cougar in your lap and...

17:50.555 --> 17:51.655
(chuckles)

17:51.723 --> 17:52.823
...voila!

17:55.960 --> 17:57.761
No!

18:00.298 --> 18:01.765
(yells)

18:01.833 --> 18:04.334
The girl in the painting
was you, wasn't it, Steve?

18:04.402 --> 18:06.403
How... H-How did you know?

18:06.471 --> 18:08.805
Because I was once in love, too.

18:16.097 --> 18:18.949
The Tender Vigilante
doesn't have...

18:19.017 --> 18:20.968
insurance.

18:22.170 --> 18:24.021
(inhales deeply)

18:25.323 --> 18:27.024
Welcome aboard, Sarah.

18:43.875 --> 18:46.810
Ms. Blanch, your limo is waiting
to take you to the airport.

18:46.878 --> 18:48.145
Thank you, Jonathan.

18:48.212 --> 18:49.946
And did you give any thought

18:50.014 --> 18:51.815
to joining my family
for Christmas dinner?

18:51.883 --> 18:54.451
We hate the thought of you
spending another holiday alone.

18:54.519 --> 18:56.586
Thank you, Jonathan,
but I'll be working.

18:56.654 --> 18:59.156
Plus, you know
I don't dine with robots.

18:59.223 --> 19:01.291
Oh, but you weren't complaining
last night

19:01.359 --> 19:04.861
when I spent the better part
of two hours eating your baaa...

19:19.477 --> 19:21.812
Broxton, before we go
to the hotel,

19:21.879 --> 19:24.181
can we make a stop first?

19:36.894 --> 19:39.863
I've seen enough, Broxton.

19:44.736 --> 19:47.370
Ms. Blanch!

19:47.438 --> 19:49.806
Back for another
concrete convention.

19:49.874 --> 19:51.708
It's been ten years

19:51.776 --> 19:53.910
and three more
Garry Marshall movies.

19:53.978 --> 19:55.378
Let me ask.

19:55.446 --> 19:57.214
Are you happy with the life
you've chosen?

19:57.281 --> 19:58.815
No.

19:58.883 --> 20:00.016
No, I'm not.

20:00.084 --> 20:02.385
Well, there's always
a way back.

20:05.757 --> 20:07.591
Uh... (clears throat)
Sorry.

20:07.658 --> 20:08.759
Here.

20:15.900 --> 20:18.802
The Tender Vigilante
doesn't have...

20:18.870 --> 20:20.804
insurance.

20:22.006 --> 20:24.107
(inhales deeply)

20:24.175 --> 20:25.909
We need to talk.

20:25.977 --> 20:27.677
I'm you from
the future.

20:27.745 --> 20:29.079
Really?

20:29.147 --> 20:31.615
When did I get
Paulie Walnut's hair?

20:31.682 --> 20:33.517
Don't get in that car.

20:37.388 --> 20:39.089
Bye, guys.
Have a good day.

20:39.157 --> 20:40.624
Wait. What
about breakfast?

20:40.691 --> 20:44.594
I'm happy to make you breakfast
every day except Thursday.

20:44.662 --> 20:46.429
Thursdays are for me.

20:48.933 --> 20:50.934
NARRATOR:
<i>And from that moment on,</i>

20:51.002 --> 20:53.703
<i>Francine made Thursday her day.</i>

20:53.771 --> 20:56.439
<i>A day to do</i>
<i>whatever she pleased.</i>

20:56.507 --> 20:58.208
<i>Yeah, girl.</i>

20:58.276 --> 20:59.576
<i>Do your thang.</i>

20:59.644 --> 21:01.978
<i>Get your Thursday on.</i>

21:07.018 --> 21:09.619
Man, was that close.

